gomodel:SYNGO_2030  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: To elucidate mechanisms that control and execute activity-dependent synaptic plasticity, GluA1 receptors with an electrophysiological tag were expressed in rat hippocampal neurons. Long-term potentiation (LTP) or increased activity of the calcium/calmodulin-dependent protein kinase II (CaMKII) induced delivery of tagged GluA1 into synapses. This effect was not diminished by mutating the CaMKII phosphorylation site on GluA1, but was blocked by mutating a predicted PDZ domain interaction site. These results show that LTP and CaMKII activity drive GluA1 to synapses by a mechanism that requires the association between GluA1 and a PDZ domain protein.. Experimental description: Personal communication with authors confirmed that over-expressed GluA1 is of rat species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_2030" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

